      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "This 2008 Porsche Cayman S features the high-revving 3.4L M97.21 flat-six power plant, paired with a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle. The mid-engine configuration provides a neutral polar moment of inertia, resulting in surgical turn-in and exceptional mid-corner stability. The hydraulic steering rack delivers unadulterated feedback, complemented by a suspension geometry that remains composed under high lateral loads. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc calipers over vented, cross-drilled rotors, ensuring consistent thermal management. This vehicle has been maintained with an emphasis on mechanical longevity, including recent cooling system refreshes and a proactive AOS replacement. It presents with minor aesthetic wear consistent with enthusiast use, but the drivetrain remains robust and the chassis harmonics are tight, offering a pure analog driving experience.",
